  <Name>k__BackingField: Romans
  fancyName: Paul's Letter to the Church of Romans
  nickname: rom
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 'The Book of Romans is a letter written by the Apostle Paul in the
    New Testament of the Bible. It is considered one of the most important theological
    works in the Christian faith. The letter is addressed to the Christians in Rome
    and discusses key concepts such as sin, salvation, and the righteousness of God.



    Paul
    emphasizes the universal need for salvation and explores the idea that all have
    sinned and fall short of God''s glory. He explains that righteousness comes through
    faith in Jesus Christ, not through adherence to the law. The letter also delves
    into the role of faith, grace, and the Holy Spirit in the believer''s life.



    Romans
    is often cited for its profound theological insights and is a foundational text
    for understanding Christian doctrine. It''s a letter that addresses both Jews
    and Gentiles, emphasizing the unity of believers in Christ and the transformative
    power of God''s grace.'
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: '  This letter is from Paul, a slave of Christ Jesus, chosen by God
        to be an apostle and sent out to preach his Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God promised this Good News long ago through his prophets in the
        holy Scriptures. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Good News is about his Son. In his earthly life he was born into
        King David\u2019s family line, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he was shown to be[[COMMENT(0)]] the Son of God when he was raised
        from the dead by the power of the Holy Spirit.[[COMMENT(1)]] He is Jesus
        Christ our Lord. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4a '
        content: Or <b>and was designated.</b>
      - number: '1:4b '
        content: Or <b>by the Spirit of holiness; </b>or <b>in the new realm of the
          Spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Through Christ, God has given us the privilege[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        authority as apostles to tell Gentiles everywhere what God has done for them,
        so that they will believe and obey him, bringing glory to his name.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: Or <b>the grace.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And you are included among those Gentiles who have been called to
        belong to Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: "God\u2019s Good News"
      content: 'I am writing to all of you in Rome who are loved by God and are called
        to be his own holy people.May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give
        you grace and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let me say first that I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all
        of you, because your faith in him is being talked about all over the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God knows how often I pray for you. Day and night I bring you and
        your needs in prayer to God, whom I serve with all my heart[[COMMENT(0)]]
        by spreading the Good News about his Son.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: Or <b>in my spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'One of the things I always pray for is the opportunity, God willing,
        to come at last to see you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I long to visit you so I can bring you some spiritual gift that
        will help you grow strong in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When we get together, I want to encourage you in your faith, but
        I also want to be encouraged by yours.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I want you to know, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] that
        I planned many times to visit you, but I was prevented until now. I want
        to work among you and see spiritual fruit, just as I have seen among other
        Gentiles. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For I have a great sense of obligation to people in both the civilized
        world and the rest of the world,[[COMMENT(0)]] to the educated and uneducated
        alike. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: Greek <b>to Greeks and barbarians.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So I am eager to come to you in Rome, too, to preach the Good News.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am not ashamed of this Good News about Christ. It is the power
        of God at work, saving everyone who believes\u2014the Jew first and also
        the Gentile.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: Greek <b>also the Greek.</b>
    - title: "God\u2019s Anger at Sin"
      content: "This Good News tells us how God makes us right in his sight. This
        is accomplished from start to finish by faith. As the Scriptures say, \u201CIt
        is through faith that a righteous person has life.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: "Or <b>\u201CThe righteous will live by faith.\u201D </b>Hab 2:4."
    - title: 
      content: 'But God shows his anger from heaven against all sinful, wicked people
        who suppress the truth by their wickedness.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: Or <b>who, by their wickedness, prevent the truth from being known.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They know the truth about God because he has made it obvious to them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For ever since the world was created, people have seen the earth
        and sky. Through everything God made, they can clearly see his invisible
        qualities\u2014his eternal power and divine nature. So they have no excuse
        for not knowing God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, they knew God, but they wouldn\u2019t worship him as God or
        even give him thanks. And they began to think up foolish ideas of what God
        was like. As a result, their minds became dark and confused. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Claiming to be wise, they instead became utter fools. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And instead of worshiping the glorious, ever-living God, they worshiped
        idols made to look like mere people and birds and animals and reptiles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So God abandoned them to do whatever shameful things their hearts
        desired. As a result, they did vile and degrading things with each other\u2019s
        bodies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They traded the truth about God for a lie. So they worshiped and
        served the things God created instead of the Creator himself, who is worthy
        of eternal praise! Amen. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why God abandoned them to their shameful desires. Even the
        women turned against the natural way to have sex and instead indulged in
        sex with each other. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the men, instead of having normal sexual relations with women,
        burned with lust for each other. Men did shameful things with other men,
        and as a result of this sin, they suffered within themselves the penalty
        they deserved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since they thought it foolish to acknowledge God, he abandoned them
        to their foolish thinking and let them do things that should never be done. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their lives became full of every kind of wickedness, sin, greed,
        hate, envy, murder, quarreling, deception, malicious behavior, and gossip. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are backstabbers, haters of God, insolent, proud, and boastful.
        They invent new ways of sinning, and they disobey their parents. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They refuse to understand, break their promises, are heartless, and
        have no mercy. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Judgment of Sin"
      content: '  You may think you can condemn such people, but you are just as
        bad, and you have no excuse! When you say they are wicked and should be punished,
        you are condemning yourself, for you who judge others do these very same
        things. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we know that God, in his justice, will punish anyone who does
        such things. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since you judge others for doing these things, why do you think you
        can avoid God\u2019s judgment when you do the same things? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you see how wonderfully kind, tolerant, and patient God
        is with you? Does this mean nothing to you? Can\u2019t you see that his kindness
        is intended to turn you from your sin?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But because you are stubborn and refuse to turn from your sin, you
        are storing up terrible punishment for yourself. For a day of anger is coming,
        when God\u2019s righteous judgment will be revealed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will judge everyone according to what they have done. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will give eternal life to those who keep on doing good, seeking
        after the glory and honor and immortality that God offers. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he will pour out his anger and wrath on those who live for themselves,
        who refuse to obey the truth and instead live lives of wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There will be trouble and calamity for everyone who keeps on doing
        what is evil\u2014for the Jew first and also for the Gentile.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        content: Greek <b>also for the Greek; </b>also in 2:10.
    - title: 
      content: "But there will be glory and honor and peace from God for all who
        do good\u2014for the Jew first and also for the Gentile. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God does not show favoritism.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Gentiles sin, they will be destroyed, even though they never
        had God\u2019s written law. And the Jews, who do have God\u2019s law, will
        be judged by that law when they fail to obey it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For merely listening to the law doesn\u2019t make us right with God.
        It is obeying the law that makes us right in his sight. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even Gentiles, who do not have God\u2019s written law, show that
        they know his law when they instinctively obey it, even without having heard
        it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They demonstrate that God\u2019s law is written in their hearts,
        for their own conscience and thoughts either accuse them or tell them they
        are doing right. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Jews and the Law
      content: "And this is the message I proclaim\u2014that the day is coming when
        God, through Christ Jesus, will judge everyone\u2019s secret life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You who call yourselves Jews are relying on God\u2019s law, and you
        boast about your special relationship with him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You know what he wants; you know what is right because you have been
        taught his law. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are convinced that you are a guide for the blind and a light
        for people who are lost in darkness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You think you can instruct the ignorant and teach children the ways
        of God. For you are certain that God\u2019s law gives you complete knowledge
        and truth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, if you teach others, why don\u2019t you teach yourself?
        You tell others not to steal, but do you steal? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You say it is wrong to commit adultery, but do you commit adultery?
        You condemn idolatry, but do you use items stolen from pagan temples?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: Greek <b>do you steal from temples?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You are so proud of knowing the law, but you dishonor God by breaking
        it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No wonder the Scriptures say, \u201CThe Gentiles blaspheme the name
        of God because of you.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:24 '
        content: Isa 52:5 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "The Jewish ceremony of circumcision has value only if you obey God\u2019s
        law. But if you don\u2019t obey God\u2019s law, you are no better off than
        an uncircumcised Gentile. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if the Gentiles obey God\u2019s law, won\u2019t God declare them
        to be his own people? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In fact, uncircumcised Gentiles who keep God\u2019s law will condemn
        you Jews who are circumcised and possess God\u2019s law but don\u2019t obey
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you are not a true Jew just because you were born of Jewish parents
        or because you have gone through the ceremony of circumcision. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: God Remains Faithful
      content: "  Then what\u2019s the advantage of being a Jew? Is there any value
        in the ceremony of circumcision? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, there are great benefits! First of all, the Jews were entrusted
        with the whole revelation of God.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Greek <b>the oracles of God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'True, some of them were unfaithful; but just because they were unfaithful,
        does that mean God will be unfaithful? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Of course not! Even if everyone else is a liar, God is true. As the
        Scriptures say about him,\u201CYou will be proved right in what you say,and
        you will win your case in court.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        content: Ps 51:4 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut,\u201D some might say, \u201Cour sinfulness serves a good
        purpose, for it helps people see how righteous God is. Isn\u2019t it unfair,
        then, for him to punish us?\u201D (This is merely a human point of view.) "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Of course not! If God were not entirely fair, how would he be qualified
        to judge the world? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut,\u201D someone might still argue, \u201Chow can God condemn
        me as a sinner if my dishonesty highlights his truthfulness and brings him
        more glory?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: All People Are Sinners
      content: "And some people even slander us by claiming that we say, \u201CThe
        more we sin, the better it is!\u201D Those who say such things deserve to
        be condemned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Well then, should we conclude that we Jews are better than others?
        No, not at all, for we have already shown that all people, whether Jews or
        Gentiles,[[COMMENT(0)]] are under the power of sin. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Greek <b>or Greeks.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CNo one is righteous\u2014not even one.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one is truly wise;no one is seeking God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All have turned away;all have become useless.No one does good,not
        a single one.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:10-12 '
        content: Pss 14:1-3; 53:1-3 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTheir talk is foul, like the stench from an open grave.Their
        tongues are filled with lies.\u201D\u201CSnake venom drips from their lips.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: Pss 5:9 (Greek version); 140:3.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTheir mouths are full of cursing and bitterness.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        content: Ps 10:7 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey rush to commit murder.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Destruction and misery always follow them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They don\u2019t know where to find peace.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15-17 '
        content: Isa 59:7-8.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey have no fear of God at all.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        content: Ps 36:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'Obviously, the law applies to those to whom it was given, for its
        purpose is to keep people from having excuses, and to show that the entire
        world is guilty before God. '
      comments: []
    - title: Christ Took Our Punishment
      content: 'For no one can ever be made right with God by doing what the law
        commands. The law simply shows us how sinful we are.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now God has shown us a way to be made right with him without
        keeping the requirements of the law, as was promised in the writings of Moses[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the prophets long ago. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: Greek <b>in the law.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'We are made right with God by placing our faith in Jesus Christ.
        And this is true for everyone who believes, no matter who we are.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For everyone has sinned; we all fall short of God\u2019s glorious
        standard. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet God, in his grace, freely makes us right in his sight. He did
        this through Christ Jesus when he freed us from the penalty for our sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God presented Jesus as the sacrifice for sin. People are made
        right with God when they believe that Jesus sacrificed his life, shedding
        his blood. This sacrifice shows that God was being fair when he held back
        and did not punish those who sinned in times past, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for he was looking ahead and including them in what he would do in
        this present time. God did this to demonstrate his righteousness, for he
        himself is fair and just, and he makes sinners right in his sight when they
        believe in Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can we boast, then, that we have done anything to be accepted by
        God? No, because our acquittal is not based on obeying the law. It is based
        on faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we are made right with God through faith and not by obeying the
        law.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After all, is God the God of the Jews only? Isn\u2019t he also the
        God of the Gentiles? Of course he is. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is only one God, and he makes people right with himself only
        by faith, whether they are Jews or Gentiles.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:30 '
        content: Greek <b>whether they are circumcised or uncircumcised.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: The Faith of Abraham
      content: '  Abraham was, humanly speaking, the founder of our Jewish nation.
        What did he discover about being made right with God? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If his good deeds had made him acceptable to God, he would have had
        something to boast about. But that was not God\u2019s way. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures tell us, \u201CAbraham believed God, and God counted
        him as righteous because of his faith.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: Gen 15:6.
    - title: 
      content: 'When people work, their wages are not a gift, but something they
        have earned. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But people are counted as righteous, not because of their work, but
        because of their faith in God who forgives sinners. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'David also spoke of this when he described the happiness of those
        who are declared righteous without working for it:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, what joy for thosewhose disobedience is forgiven,whose
        sins are put out of sight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, what joy for thosewhose record the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has cleared of sin.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7-8 '
        content: Ps 32:1-2 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, is this blessing only for the Jews, or is it also for uncircumcised
        Gentiles?[[COMMENT(0)]] Well, we have been saying that Abraham was counted
        as righteous by God because of his faith. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: Greek <b>is this blessing only for the circumcised, or is it also
          for the uncircumcised?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But how did this happen? Was he counted as righteous only after he
        was circumcised, or was it before he was circumcised? Clearly, God accepted
        Abraham before he was circumcised!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Circumcision was a sign that Abraham already had faith and that God
        had already accepted him and declared him to be righteous\u2014even before
        he was circumcised. So Abraham is the spiritual father of those who have
        faith but have not been circumcised. They are counted as righteous because
        of their faith. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And Abraham is also the spiritual father of those who have been circumcised,
        but only if they have the same kind of faith Abraham had before he was circumcised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Clearly, God\u2019s promise to give the whole earth to Abraham and
        his descendants was based not on his obedience to God\u2019s law, but on
        a right relationship with God that comes by faith. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If God\u2019s promise is only for those who obey the law, then faith
        is not necessary and the promise is pointless. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the law always brings punishment on those who try to obey it.
        (The only way to avoid breaking the law is to have no law to break!)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the promise is received by faith. It is given as a free gift.
        And we are all certain to receive it, whether or not we live according to
        the law of Moses, if we have faith like Abraham\u2019s. For Abraham is the
        father of all who believe. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is what the Scriptures mean when God told him, \u201CI have
        made you the father of many nations.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] This happened because
        Abraham believed in the God who brings the dead back to life and who creates
        new things out of nothing.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: Gen 17:5.
    - title: 
      content: "Even when there was no reason for hope, Abraham kept hoping\u2014believing
        that he would become the father of many nations. For God had said to him,
        \u201CThat\u2019s how many descendants you will have!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        content: Gen 15:5.
    - title: 
      content: "And Abraham\u2019s faith did not weaken, even though, at about 100
        years of age, he figured his body was as good as dead\u2014and so was Sarah\u2019s
        womb.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Abraham never wavered in believing God\u2019s promise. In fact, his
        faith grew stronger, and in this he brought glory to God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He was fully convinced that God is able to do whatever he promises. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And because of Abraham\u2019s faith, God counted him as righteous. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when God counted him as righteous, it wasn\u2019t just for Abraham\u2019s
        benefit. It was recorded "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for our benefit, too, assuring us that God will also count us as
        righteous if we believe in him, the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the
        dead. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Faith Brings Joy
      content: "  Therefore, since we have been made right in God\u2019s sight by
        faith, we have peace[[COMMENT(0)]] with God because of what Jesus Christ
        our Lord has done for us. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>let us have peace.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Because of our faith, Christ has brought us into this place of undeserved
        privilege where we now stand, and we confidently and joyfully look forward
        to sharing God\u2019s glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We can rejoice, too, when we run into problems and trials, for we
        know that they help us develop endurance. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And endurance develops strength of character, and character strengthens
        our confident hope of salvation. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this hope will not lead to disappointment. For we know how dearly
        God loves us, because he has given us the Holy Spirit to fill our hearts
        with his love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When we were utterly helpless, Christ came at just the right time
        and died for us sinners. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, most people would not be willing to die for an upright person,
        though someone might perhaps be willing to die for a person who is especially
        good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God showed his great love for us by sending Christ to die for
        us while we were still sinners. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And since we have been made right in God\u2019s sight by the blood
        of Christ, he will certainly save us from God\u2019s condemnation. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For since our friendship with God was restored by the death of his
        Son while we were still his enemies, we will certainly be saved through the
        life of his Son. '
      comments: []
    - title: Adam and Christ Contrasted
      content: 'So now we can rejoice in our wonderful new relationship with God
        because our Lord Jesus Christ has made us friends of God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Adam sinned, sin entered the world. Adam\u2019s sin brought
        death, so death spread to everyone, for everyone sinned. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, people sinned even before the law was given. But it was not
        counted as sin because there was not yet any law to break. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Still, everyone died\u2014from the time of Adam to the time of Moses\u2014even
        those who did not disobey an explicit commandment of God, as Adam did. Now
        Adam is a symbol, a representation of Christ, who was yet to come. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But there is a great difference between Adam\u2019s sin and God\u2019s
        gracious gift. For the sin of this one man, Adam, brought death to many.
        But even greater is God\u2019s wonderful grace and his gift of forgiveness
        to many through this other man, Jesus Christ. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the result of God\u2019s gracious gift is very different from
        the result of that one man\u2019s sin. For Adam\u2019s sin led to condemnation,
        but God\u2019s free gift leads to our being made right with God, even though
        we are guilty of many sins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the sin of this one man, Adam, caused death to rule over many.
        But even greater is God\u2019s wonderful grace and his gift of righteousness,
        for all who receive it will live in triumph over sin and death through this
        one man, Jesus Christ.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, Adam\u2019s one sin brings condemnation for everyone, but Christ\u2019s
        one act of righteousness brings a right relationship with God and new life
        for everyone. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because one person disobeyed God, many became sinners. But because
        one other person obeyed God, many will be made righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s law was given so that all people could see how sinful
        they were. But as people sinned more and more, God\u2019s wonderful grace
        became more abundant. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Sin\u2019s Power Is Broken"
      content: '  Well then, should we keep on sinning so that God can show us more
        and more of his wonderful grace? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Of course not! Since we have died to sin, how can we continue to
        live in it? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Or have you forgotten that when we were joined with Christ Jesus
        in baptism, we joined him in his death? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we died and were buried with Christ by baptism. And just as Christ
        was raised from the dead by the glorious power of the Father, now we also
        may live new lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since we have been united with him in his death, we will also be
        raised to life as he was. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We know that our old sinful selves were crucified with Christ so
        that sin might lose its power in our lives. We are no longer slaves to sin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For when we died with Christ we were set free from the power of sin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And since we died with Christ, we know we will also live with him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are sure of this because Christ was raised from the dead, and
        he will never die again. Death no longer has any power over him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he died, he died once to break the power of sin. But now that
        he lives, he lives for the glory of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you also should consider yourselves to be dead to the power of
        sin and alive to God through Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not let sin control the way you live;[[COMMENT(0)]] do not give
        in to sinful desires. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:12 '
        content: Or <b>Do not let sin reign in your body, which is subject to death.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not let any part of your body become an instrument of evil to
        serve sin. Instead, give yourselves completely to God, for you were dead,
        but now you have new life. So use your whole body as an instrument to do
        what is right for the glory of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sin is no longer your master, for you no longer live under the requirements
        of the law. Instead, you live under the freedom of God\u2019s grace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, since God\u2019s grace has set us free from the law, does
        that mean we can go on sinning? Of course not! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you realize that you become the slave of whatever you
        choose to obey? You can be a slave to sin, which leads to death, or you can
        choose to obey God, which leads to righteous living. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Thank God! Once you were slaves of sin, but now you wholeheartedly
        obey this teaching we have given you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now you are free from your slavery to sin, and you have become slaves
        to righteous living.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of the weakness of your human nature, I am using the illustration
        of slavery to help you understand all this. Previously, you let yourselves
        be slaves to impurity and lawlessness, which led ever deeper into sin. Now
        you must give yourselves to be slaves to righteous living so that you will
        become holy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you were slaves to sin, you were free from the obligation to
        do right. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And what was the result? You are now ashamed of the things you used
        to do, things that end in eternal doom. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now you are free from the power of sin and have become slaves
        of God. Now you do those things that lead to holiness and result in eternal
        life. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: No Longer Bound to the Law
      content: "  Now, dear brothers and sisters[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014you who are familiar
        with the law\u2014don\u2019t you know that the law applies only while a person
        is living? "
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 7:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'For example, when a woman marries, the law binds her to her husband
        as long as he is alive. But if he dies, the laws of marriage no longer apply
        to her. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So while her husband is alive, she would be committing adultery if
        she married another man. But if her husband dies, she is free from that law
        and does not commit adultery when she remarries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So, my dear brothers and sisters, this is the point: You died to
        the power of the law when you died with Christ. And now you are united with
        the one who was raised from the dead. As a result, we can produce a harvest
        of good deeds for God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When we were controlled by our old nature,[[COMMENT(0)]] sinful desires
        were at work within us, and the law aroused these evil desires that produced
        a harvest of sinful deeds, resulting in death. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: Greek <b>When we were in the flesh.</b>
    - title: "God\u2019s Law Reveals Our Sin"
      content: 'But now we have been released from the law, for we died to it and
        are no longer captive to its power. Now we can serve God, not in the old
        way of obeying the letter of the law, but in the new way of living in the
        Spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, am I suggesting that the law of God is sinful? Of course
        not! In fact, it was the law that showed me my sin. I would never have known
        that coveting is wrong if the law had not said, \u201CYou must not covet.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:7 '
        content: Exod 20:17; Deut 5:21.
    - title: 
      content: 'But sin used this command to arouse all kinds of covetous desires
        within me! If there were no law, sin would not have that power. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At one time I lived without understanding the law. But when I learned
        the command not to covet, for instance, the power of sin came to life, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and I died. So I discovered that the law\u2019s commands, which were
        supposed to bring life, brought spiritual death instead. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sin took advantage of those commands and deceived me; it used the
        commands to kill me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But still, the law itself is holy, and its commands are holy and
        right and good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Struggling with Sin
      content: "But how can that be? Did the law, which is good, cause my death?
        Of course not! Sin used what was good to bring about my condemnation to death.
        So we can see how terrible sin really is. It uses God\u2019s good commands
        for its own evil purposes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the trouble is not with the law, for it is spiritual and good.
        The trouble is with me, for I am all too human, a slave to sin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I don\u2019t really understand myself, for I want to do what is right,
        but I don\u2019t do it. Instead, I do what I hate. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if I know that what I am doing is wrong, this shows that I agree
        that the law is good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I am not the one doing wrong; it is sin living in me that does
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I know that nothing good lives in me, that is, in my sinful nature.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        I want to do what is right, but I can\u2019t. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:18 '
        content: Greek <b>my flesh; </b>also in 7:25.
    - title: 
      content: "I want to do what is good, but I don\u2019t. I don\u2019t want to
        do what is wrong, but I do it anyway. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if I do what I don\u2019t want to do, I am not really the one
        doing wrong; it is sin living in me that does it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have discovered this principle of life\u2014that when I want to
        do what is right, I inevitably do what is wrong. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I love God\u2019s law with all my heart. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But there is another power[[COMMENT(0)]] within me that is at war
        with my mind. This power makes me a slave to the sin that is still within
        me. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: Greek <b>law; </b>also in 7:23b.
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, what a miserable person I am! Who will free me from this life
        that is dominated by sin and death? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Life in the Spirit
      content: '  So now there is no condemnation for those who belong to Christ
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And because you belong to him, the power[[COMMENT(0)]] of the life-giving
        Spirit has freed you[[COMMENT(1)]] from the power of sin that leads to death. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:2a '
        content: Greek <b>the law; </b>also in 8:2b.
      - number: '8:2b '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>me.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The law of Moses was unable to save us because of the weakness of
        our sinful nature.[[COMMENT(0)]] So God did what the law could not do. He
        sent his own Son in a body like the bodies we sinners have. And in that body
        God declared an end to sin\u2019s control over us by giving his Son as a
        sacrifice for our sins. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: Greek <b>our flesh; </b>similarly in 8:4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 12.
    - title: 
      content: 'He did this so that the just requirement of the law would be fully
        satisfied for us, who no longer follow our sinful nature but instead follow
        the Spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who are dominated by the sinful nature think about sinful things,
        but those who are controlled by the Holy Spirit think about things that please
        the Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So letting your sinful nature control your mind leads to death. But
        letting the Spirit control your mind leads to life and peace. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the sinful nature is always hostile to God. It never did obey
        God\u2019s laws, and it never will. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s why those who are still under the control of their sinful
        nature can never please God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are not controlled by your sinful nature. You are controlled
        by the Spirit if you have the Spirit of God living in you. (And remember
        that those who do not have the Spirit of Christ living in them do not belong
        to him at all.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And Christ lives within you, so even though your body will die because
        of sin, the Spirit gives you life[[COMMENT(0)]] because you have been made
        right with God. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: Or <b>your spirit is alive.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The Spirit of God, who raised Jesus from the dead, lives in you.
        And just as God raised Christ Jesus from the dead, he will give life to your
        mortal bodies by this same Spirit living within you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] you have no obligation
        to do what your sinful nature urges you to do. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:12 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 8:29.
    - title: 
      content: 'For if you live by its dictates, you will die. But if through the
        power of the Spirit you put to death the deeds of your sinful nature,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        you will live. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:13 '
        content: Greek <b>deeds of the body.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For all who are led by the Spirit of God are children[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:14 '
        content: Greek <b>sons; </b>also in 8:19.
    - title: 
      content: "So you have not received a spirit that makes you fearful slaves.
        Instead, you received God\u2019s Spirit when he adopted you as his own children.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Now we call him, \u201CAbba, Father.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:15a '
        content: Greek <b>you received a spirit of sonship.</b>
      - number: '8:15b '
        content: "<b>Abba </b>is an Aramaic term for \u201Cfather.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "For his Spirit joins with our spirit to affirm that we are God\u2019s
        children. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Future Glory
      content: "And since we are his children, we are his heirs. In fact, together
        with Christ we are heirs of God\u2019s glory. But if we are to share his
        glory, we must also share his suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet what we suffer now is nothing compared to the glory he will reveal
        to us later. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For all creation is waiting eagerly for that future day when God
        will reveal who his children really are. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Against its will, all creation was subjected to God\u2019s curse.
        But with eager hope, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the creation looks forward to the day when it will join God\u2019s
        children in glorious freedom from death and decay. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we know that all creation has been groaning as in the pains of
        childbirth right up to the present time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we believers also groan, even though we have the Holy Spirit
        within us as a foretaste of future glory, for we long for our bodies to be
        released from sin and suffering. We, too, wait with eager hope for the day
        when God will give us our full rights as his adopted children,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        including the new bodies he has promised us. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:23 '
        content: Greek <b>wait anxiously for sonship.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "We were given this hope when we were saved. (If we already have something,
        we don\u2019t need to hope[[COMMENT(0)]] for it. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:24 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>wait.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But if we look forward to something we don\u2019t yet have, we must
        wait patiently and confidently.)  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the Holy Spirit helps us in our weakness. For example, we don\u2019t
        know what God wants us to pray for. But the Holy Spirit prays for us with
        groanings that cannot be expressed in words. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the Father who knows all hearts knows what the Spirit is saying,
        for the Spirit pleads for us believers[[COMMENT(0)]] in harmony with God\u2019s
        own will. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:27 '
        content: "Greek <b>for God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'And we know that God causes everything to work together[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for the good of those who love God and are called according to his purpose
        for them. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:28 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>And we know that everything works together.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For God knew his people in advance, and he chose them to become like
        his Son, so that his Son would be the firstborn[[COMMENT(0)]] among many
        brothers and sisters. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:29 '
        content: Or <b>would be supreme.</b>
    - title: "Nothing Can Separate Us from God\u2019s Love"
      content: 'And having chosen them, he called them to come to him. And having
        called them, he gave them right standing with himself. And having given them
        right standing, he gave them his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What shall we say about such wonderful things as these? If God is
        for us, who can ever be against us? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since he did not spare even his own Son but gave him up for us all,
        won\u2019t he also give us everything else? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who dares accuse us whom God has chosen for his own? No one\u2014for
        God himself has given us right standing with himself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who then will condemn us? No one\u2014for Christ Jesus died for us
        and was raised to life for us, and he is sitting in the place of honor at
        God\u2019s right hand, pleading for us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can anything ever separate us from Christ\u2019s love? Does it mean
        he no longer loves us if we have trouble or calamity, or are persecuted,
        or hungry, or destitute, or in danger, or threatened with death? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "(As the Scriptures say, \u201CFor your sake we are killed every day;
        we are being slaughtered like sheep.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]) "
      comments:
      - number: '8:36 '
        content: Ps 44:22.
    - title: 
      content: 'No, despite all these things, overwhelming victory is ours through
        Christ, who loved us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I am convinced that nothing can ever separate us from God\u2019s
        love. Neither death nor life, neither angels nor demons,[[COMMENT(0)]] neither
        our fears for today nor our worries about tomorrow\u2014not even the powers
        of hell can separate us from God\u2019s love. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:38 '
        content: Greek <b>nor rulers.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Selection of Israel"
      content: '  With Christ as my witness, I speak with utter truthfulness. My
        conscience and the Holy Spirit confirm it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart is filled with bitter sorrow and unending grief '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for my people, my Jewish brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]] I would
        be willing to be forever cursed\u2014cut off from Christ!\u2014if that would
        save them. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: Greek <b>my brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They are the people of Israel, chosen to be God\u2019s adopted children.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        God revealed his glory to them. He made covenants with them and gave them
        his law. He gave them the privilege of worshiping him and receiving his wonderful
        promises. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:4 '
        content: Greek <b>chosen for sonship.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob are their ancestors, and Christ himself
        was an Israelite as far as his human nature is concerned. And he is God,
        the one who rules over everything and is worthy of eternal praise! Amen.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:5 '
        content: Or <b>May God, the one who rules over everything, be praised forever.
          Amen.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, has God failed to fulfill his promise to Israel? No, for
        not all who are born into the nation of Israel are truly members of God\u2019s
        people! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Being descendants of Abraham doesn\u2019t make them truly Abraham\u2019s
        children. For the Scriptures say, \u201CIsaac is the son through whom your
        descendants will be counted,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] though Abraham had other
        children, too. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: Gen 21:12.
    - title: 
      content: "This means that Abraham\u2019s physical descendants are not necessarily
        children of God. Only the children of the promise are considered to be Abraham\u2019s
        children. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God had promised, \u201CI will return about this time next year,
        and Sarah will have a son.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        content: Gen 18:10, 14.
    - title: 
      content: 'This son was our ancestor Isaac. When he married Rebekah, she gave
        birth to twins.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:10 '
        content: Greek <b>she conceived children through this one man.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But before they were born, before they had done anything good or
        bad, she received a message from God. (This message shows that God chooses
        people according to his own purposes; '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he calls people, but not according to their good or bad works.) She
        was told, \u201CYour older son will serve your younger son.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:12 '
        content: Gen 25:23.
    - title: 
      content: "In the words of the Scriptures, \u201CI loved Jacob, but I rejected
        Esau.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: Mal 1:2-3.
    - title: 
      content: 'Are we saying, then, that God was unfair? Of course not! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God said to Moses,\u201CI will show mercy to anyone I choose,and
        I will show compassion to anyone I choose.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:15 '
        content: Exod 33:19.
    - title: 
      content: 'So it is God who decides to show mercy. We can neither choose it
        nor work for it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures say that God told Pharaoh, \u201CI have appointed
        you for the very purpose of displaying my power in you and to spread my fame
        throughout the earth.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        content: Exod 9:16 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'So you see, God chooses to show mercy to some, and he chooses to
        harden the hearts of others so they refuse to listen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well then, you might say, \u201CWhy does God blame people for not
        responding? Haven\u2019t they simply done what he makes them do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, don\u2019t say that. Who are you, a mere human being, to argue
        with God? Should the thing that was created say to the one who created it,
        \u201CWhy have you made me like this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When a potter makes jars out of clay, doesn\u2019t he have a right
        to use the same lump of clay to make one jar for decoration and another to
        throw garbage into? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, even though God has the right to show his anger
        and his power, he is very patient with those on whom his anger falls, who
        are destined for destruction. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He does this to make the riches of his glory shine even brighter
        on those to whom he shows mercy, who were prepared in advance for glory. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And we are among those whom he selected, both from the Jews and from
        the Gentiles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Concerning the Gentiles, God says in the prophecy of Hosea,\u201CThose
        who were not my people,I will now call my people.And I will love thosewhom
        I did not love before.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:25 '
        content: Hos 2:23.
    - title: 
      content: "And,\u201CThen, at the place where they were told,\u2018You are not
        my people,\u2019there they will be called\u2018children of the living God.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        content: Greek <b>sons of the living God. </b>Hos 1:10.
    - title: 
      content: "And concerning Israel, Isaiah the prophet cried out,\u201CThough
        the people of Israel are as numerous as the sand of the seashore,only a remnant
        will be saved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will carry out his sentence upon
        the earthquickly and with finality.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:27-28 '
        content: Isa 10:22-23 (Greek version).
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Unbelief"
      content: "And Isaiah said the same thing in another place:\u201CIf the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armieshad not spared a few of our children,we would have
        been wiped out like Sodom,destroyed like Gomorrah.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:29 '
        content: Isa 1:9 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "What does all this mean? Even though the Gentiles were not trying
        to follow God\u2019s standards, they were made right with God. And it was
        by faith that this took place. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the people of Israel, who tried so hard to get right with God
        by keeping the law, never succeeded. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why not? Because they were trying to get right with God by keeping
        the law[[COMMENT(0)]] instead of by trusting in him. They stumbled over the
        great rock in their path. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:32 '
        content: Greek <b>by works.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] the longing of my heart
        and my prayer to God is for the people of Israel to be saved. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I know what enthusiasm they have for God, but it is misdirected zeal. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they don\u2019t understand God\u2019s way of making people right
        with himself. Refusing to accept God\u2019s way, they cling to their own
        way of getting right with God by trying to keep the law. "
      comments: []
    - title: Salvation Is for Everyone
      content: 'For Christ has already accomplished the purpose for which the law
        was given.[[COMMENT(0)]] As a result, all who believe in him are made right
        with God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: Or <b>For Christ is the end of the law.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For Moses writes that the law\u2019s way of making a person right
        with God requires obedience to all of its commands.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: See Lev 18:5.
    - title: 
      content: "But faith\u2019s way of getting right with God says, \u201CDon\u2019t
        say in your heart, \u2018Who will go up to heaven?\u2019 (to bring Christ
        down to earth). "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t say, \u2018Who will go down to the place of the dead?\u2019
        (to bring Christ back to life again).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In fact, it says,\u201CThe message is very close at hand;it is on
        your lips and in your heart.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]And that message is the very
        message about faith that we preach: "
      comments:
      - number: '10:6-8 '
        content: Deut 30:12-14.
    - title: 
      content: 'If you openly declare that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart
        that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For it is by believing in your heart that you are made right with
        God, and it is by openly declaring your faith that you are saved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures tell us, \u201CAnyone who trusts in him will never
        be disgraced.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11 '
        content: Isa 28:16 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'Jew and Gentile[[COMMENT(0)]] are the same in this respect. They
        have the same Lord, who gives generously to all who call on him. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:12 '
        content: Greek <b>and Greek.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For \u201CEveryone who calls on the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be saved.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:13 '
        content: Joel 2:32.
    - title: 
      content: 'But how can they call on him to save them unless they believe in
        him? And how can they believe in him if they have never heard about him?
        And how can they hear about him unless someone tells them? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And how will anyone go and tell them without being sent? That is
        why the Scriptures say, \u201CHow beautiful are the feet of messengers who
        bring good news!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:15 '
        content: Isa 52:7.
    - title: 
      content: "But not everyone welcomes the Good News, for Isaiah the prophet said,
        \u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who has believed our message?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: Isa 53:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'So faith comes from hearing, that is, hearing the Good News about
        Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I ask, have the people of Israel actually heard the message?
        Yes, they have:\u201CThe message has gone throughout the earth,and the words
        to all the world.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:18 '
        content: Ps 19:4.
    - title: 
      content: "But I ask, did the people of Israel really understand? Yes, they
        did, for even in the time of Moses, God said,\u201CI will rouse your jealousy
        through people who are not even a nation.I will provoke your anger through
        the foolish Gentiles.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        content: Deut 32:21.
    - title: 
      content: "And later Isaiah spoke boldly for God, saying,\u201CI was found by
        people who were not looking for me.I showed myself to those who were not
        asking for me.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:20 '
        content: Isa 65:1 (Greek version).
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Mercy on Israel"
      content: '  I ask, then, has God rejected his own people, the nation of Israel?
        Of course not! I myself am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham and a member
        of the tribe of Benjamin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, God has not rejected his own people, whom he chose from the very
        beginning. Do you realize what the Scriptures say about this? Elijah the
        prophet complained to God about the people of Israel and said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, they have killed your prophets
        and torn down your altars. I am the only one left, and now they are trying
        to kill me, too.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:3 '
        content: 1 Kgs 19:10, 14.
    - title: 
      content: "And do you remember God\u2019s reply? He said, \u201CNo, I have 7,000
        others who have never bowed down to Baal!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: 1 Kgs 19:18.
    - title: 
      content: "It is the same today, for a few of the people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]
        have remained faithful because of God\u2019s grace\u2014his undeserved kindness
        in choosing them. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:5 '
        content: Greek <b>for a remnant.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And since it is through God\u2019s kindness, then it is not by their
        good works. For in that case, God\u2019s grace would not be what it really
        is\u2014free and undeserved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So this is the situation: Most of the people of Israel have not found
        the favor of God they are looking for so earnestly. A few have\u2014the ones
        God has chosen\u2014but the hearts of the rest were hardened. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CGod has put them into a deep sleep.To
        this day he has shut their eyes so they do not see,and closed their ears
        so they do not hear.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: Isa 29:10; Deut 29:4.
    - title: 
      content: "Likewise, David said,\u201CLet their bountiful table become a snare,a
        trap that makes them think all is well.Let their blessings cause them to
        stumble,and let them get what they deserve.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let their eyes go blind so they cannot see,and let their backs be
        bent forever.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:9-10 '
        content: Ps 69:22-23 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "Did God\u2019s people stumble and fall beyond recovery? Of course
        not! They were disobedient, so God made salvation available to the Gentiles.
        But he wanted his own people to become jealous and claim it for themselves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now if the Gentiles were enriched because the people of Israel turned
        down God\u2019s offer of salvation, think how much greater a blessing the
        world will share when they finally accept it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am saying all this especially for you Gentiles. God has appointed
        me as the apostle to the Gentiles. I stress this, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for I want somehow to make the people of Israel jealous of what you
        Gentiles have, so I might save some of them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For since their rejection meant that God offered salvation to the
        rest of the world, their acceptance will be even more wonderful. It will
        be life for those who were dead! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And since Abraham and the other patriarchs were holy, their descendants
        will also be holy\u2014just as the entire batch of dough is holy because
        the portion given as an offering is holy. For if the roots of the tree are
        holy, the branches will be, too.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But some of these branches from Abraham\u2019s tree\u2014some of
        the people of Israel\u2014have been broken off. And you Gentiles, who were
        branches from a wild olive tree, have been grafted in. So now you also receive
        the blessing God has promised Abraham and his children, sharing in the rich
        nourishment from the root of God\u2019s special olive tree. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you must not brag about being grafted in to replace the branches
        that were broken off. You are just a branch, not the root.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWell,\u201D you may say, \u201Cthose branches were broken off
        to make room for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, but remember\u2014those branches were broken off because they
        didn\u2019t believe in Christ, and you are there because you do believe.
        So don\u2019t think highly of yourself, but fear what could happen. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if God did not spare the original branches, he won\u2019t[[COMMENT(0)]]
        spare you either.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:21 '
        content: "Some manuscripts read <b>perhaps he won\u2019t.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Notice how God is both kind and severe. He is severe toward those
        who disobeyed, but kind to you if you continue to trust in his kindness.
        But if you stop trusting, you also will be cut off. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if the people of Israel turn from their unbelief, they will be
        grafted in again, for God has the power to graft them back into the tree. '
      comments: []
    - title: "God\u2019s Mercy Is for Everyone"
      content: 'You, by nature, were a branch cut from a wild olive tree. So if God
        was willing to do something contrary to nature by grafting you into his cultivated
        tree, he will be far more eager to graft the original branches back into
        the tree where they belong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I want you to understand this mystery, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        so that you will not feel proud about yourselves. Some of the people of Israel
        have hard hearts, but this will last only until the full number of Gentiles
        comes to Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:25 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And so all Israel will be saved. As the Scriptures say,\u201CThe
        one who rescues will come from Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]and he will turn Israel[[COMMENT(1)]]
        away from ungodliness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:26a '
        content: Greek <b>from Zion.</b>
      - number: '11:26b '
        content: Greek <b>Jacob.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And this is my covenant with them,that I will take away their sins.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:26-27 '
        content: Isa 59:20-21; 27:9 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'Many of the people of Israel are now enemies of the Good News, and
        this benefits you Gentiles. Yet they are still the people he loves because
        he chose their ancestors Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God\u2019s gifts and his call can never be withdrawn. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Once, you Gentiles were rebels against God, but when the people of
        Israel rebelled against him, God was merciful to you instead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now they are the rebels, and God\u2019s mercy has come to you so
        that they, too, will share[[COMMENT(0)]] in God\u2019s mercy. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:31 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>will now share; </b>still others read
          <b>will someday share.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For God has imprisoned everyone in disobedience so he could have
        mercy on everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, how great are God\u2019s riches and wisdom and knowledge! How
        impossible it is for us to understand his decisions and his ways!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For who can know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s thoughts?Who
        knows enough to give him advice?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:34 '
        content: Isa 40:13 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'And who has given him so muchthat he needs to pay it back?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:35 '
        content: See Job 41:11.
  - verses:
    - title: A Living Sacrifice to God
      content: "  And so, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] I plead with you
        to give your bodies to God because of all he has done for you. Let them be
        a living and holy sacrifice\u2014the kind he will find acceptable. This is
        truly the way to worship him.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:1a '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
      - number: '12:1b '
        content: Or <b>This is your spiritual worship; </b>or <b>This is your reasonable
          service.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t copy the behavior and customs of this world, but let God
        transform you into a new person by changing the way you think. Then you will
        learn to know God\u2019s will for you, which is good and pleasing and perfect.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because of the privilege and authority[[COMMENT(0)]] God has given
        me, I give each of you this warning: Don\u2019t think you are better than
        you really are. Be honest in your evaluation of yourselves, measuring yourselves
        by the faith God has given us.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:3a '
        content: Or <b>Because of the grace; </b>compare 1:5.
      - number: '12:3b '
        content: Or <b>by the faith God has given you; </b>or <b>by the standard
          of our God-given faith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as our bodies have many parts and each part has a special function, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "so it is with Christ\u2019s body. We are many parts of one body,
        and we all belong to each other.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In his grace, God has given us different gifts for doing certain
        things well. So if God has given you the ability to prophesy, speak out with
        as much faith as God has given you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If your gift is serving others, serve them well. If you are a teacher,
        teach well. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If your gift is to encourage others, be encouraging. If it is giving,
        give generously. If God has given you leadership ability, take the responsibility
        seriously. And if you have a gift for showing kindness to others, do it gladly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t just pretend to love others. Really love them. Hate what
        is wrong. Hold tightly to what is good. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Love each other with genuine affection,[[COMMENT(0)]] and take delight
        in honoring each other. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:10 '
        content: Greek <b>with brotherly love.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Never be lazy, but work hard and serve the Lord enthusiastically.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:11 '
        content: Or <b>but serve the Lord with a zealous spirit; </b>or <b>but let
          the Spirit excite you as you serve the Lord.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Rejoice in our confident hope. Be patient in trouble, and keep on
        praying. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When God\u2019s people are in need, be ready to help them. Always
        be eager to practice hospitality.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bless those who persecute you. Don\u2019t curse them; pray that God
        will bless them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be happy with those who are happy, and weep with those who weep. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Live in harmony with each other. Don\u2019t be too proud to enjoy
        the company of ordinary people. And don\u2019t think you know it all!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never pay back evil with more evil. Do things in such a way that
        everyone can see you are honorable. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do all that you can to live in peace with everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear friends, never take revenge. Leave that to the righteous anger
        of God. For the Scriptures say,\u201CI will take revenge;I will pay them
        back,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:19 '
        content: Deut 32:35.
    - title: 
      content: "Instead,\u201CIf your enemies are hungry, feed them.If they are thirsty,
        give them something to drink.In doing this, you will heapburning coals of
        shame on their heads.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:20 '
        content: Prov 25:21-22.
  - verses:
    - title: Respect for Authority
      content: '  Everyone must submit to governing authorities. For all authority
        comes from God, and those in positions of authority have been placed there
        by God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So anyone who rebels against authority is rebelling against what
        God has instituted, and they will be punished. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the authorities do not strike fear in people who are doing right,
        but in those who are doing wrong. Would you like to live without fear of
        the authorities? Do what is right, and they will honor you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The authorities are God\u2019s servants, sent for your good. But
        if you are doing wrong, of course you should be afraid, for they have the
        power to punish you. They are God\u2019s servants, sent for the very purpose
        of punishing those who do what is wrong. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you must submit to them, not only to avoid punishment, but also
        to keep a clear conscience.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pay your taxes, too, for these same reasons. For government workers
        need to be paid. They are serving God in what they do. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Love Fulfills God\u2019s Requirements"
      content: 'Give to everyone what you owe them: Pay your taxes and government
        fees to those who collect them, and give respect and honor to those who are
        in authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Owe nothing to anyone\u2014except for your obligation to love one
        another. If you love your neighbor, you will fulfill the requirements of
        God\u2019s law. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the commandments say, \u201CYou must not commit adultery. You
        must not murder. You must not steal. You must not covet.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        These\u2014and other such commandments\u2014are summed up in this one commandment:
        \u201CLove your neighbor as yourself.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:9a '
        content: Exod 20:13-15, 17.
      - number: '13:9b '
        content: Lev 19:18.
    - title: 
      content: "Love does no wrong to others, so love fulfills the requirements of
        God\u2019s law.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is all the more urgent, for you know how late it is; time is
        running out. Wake up, for our salvation is nearer now than when we first
        believed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The night is almost gone; the day of salvation will soon be here.
        So remove your dark deeds like dirty clothes, and put on the shining armor
        of right living. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because we belong to the day, we must live decent lives for all to
        see. Don\u2019t participate in the darkness of wild parties and drunkenness,
        or in sexual promiscuity and immoral living, or in quarreling and jealousy. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Danger of Criticism
      content: "  Accept other believers who are weak in faith, and don\u2019t argue
        with them about what they think is right or wrong. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For instance, one person believes it\u2019s all right to eat anything.
        But another believer with a sensitive conscience will eat only vegetables. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who feel free to eat anything must not look down on those who
        don\u2019t. And those who don\u2019t eat certain foods must not condemn those
        who do, for God has accepted them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who are you to condemn someone else\u2019s servants? Their own master
        will judge whether they stand or fall. And with the Lord\u2019s help, they
        will stand and receive his approval.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, some think one day is more holy than another day,
        while others think every day is alike. You should each be fully convinced
        that whichever day you choose is acceptable. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who worship the Lord on a special day do it to honor him. Those
        who eat any kind of food do so to honor the Lord, since they give thanks
        to God before eating. And those who refuse to eat certain foods also want
        to please the Lord and give thanks to God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For we don\u2019t live for ourselves or die for ourselves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If we live, it\u2019s to honor the Lord. And if we die, it\u2019s
        to honor the Lord. So whether we live or die, we belong to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Christ died and rose again for this very purpose\u2014to be Lord
        both of the living and of the dead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So why do you condemn another believer[[COMMENT(0)]]? Why do you
        look down on another believer? Remember, we will all stand before the judgment
        seat of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:10 '
        content: Greek <b>your brother; </b>also in 14:10b, 13, 15, 21.
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures say,\u201C\u2018As surely as I live,\u2019 says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2018every knee will bend to me,and every
        tongue will declare allegiance to God.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:11 '
        content: Or <b>declare praise for God. </b>Isa 49:18; 45:23 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, each of us will give a personal account to God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So let\u2019s stop condemning each other. Decide instead to live
        in such a way that you will not cause another believer to stumble and fall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know and am convinced on the authority of the Lord Jesus that no
        food, in and of itself, is wrong to eat. But if someone believes it is wrong,
        then for that person it is wrong. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if another believer is distressed by what you eat, you are not
        acting in love if you eat it. Don\u2019t let your eating ruin someone for
        whom Christ died. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will not be criticized for doing something you believe is
        good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Kingdom of God is not a matter of what we eat or drink, but
        of living a life of goodness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you serve Christ with this attitude, you will please God, and
        others will approve of you, too. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So then, let us aim for harmony in the church and try to build each
        other up.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t tear apart the work of God over what you eat. Remember,
        all foods are acceptable, but it is wrong to eat something if it makes another
        person stumble. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is better not to eat meat or drink wine or do anything else if
        it might cause another believer to stumble.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:21 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>to stumble or be offended or be weakened.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "You may believe there\u2019s nothing wrong with what you are doing,
        but keep it between yourself and God. Blessed are those who don\u2019t feel
        guilty for doing something they have decided is right. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Living to Please Others
      content: '  We who are strong must be considerate of those who are sensitive
        about things like this. We must not just please ourselves. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We should help others do what is right and build them up in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For even Christ didn\u2019t live to please himself. As the Scriptures
        say, \u201CThe insults of those who insult you, O God, have fallen on me.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:3 '
        content: Greek <b>who insult you have fallen on me. </b>Ps 69:9.
    - title: 
      content: "Such things were written in the Scriptures long ago to teach us.
        And the Scriptures give us hope and encouragement as we wait patiently for
        God\u2019s promises to be fulfilled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May God, who gives this patience and encouragement, help you live
        in complete harmony with each other, as is fitting for followers of Christ
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all of you can join together with one voice, giving praise and
        glory to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, accept each other just as Christ has accepted you so that
        God will be given glory. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that Christ came as a servant to the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to show that God is true to the promises he made to their ancestors. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:8 '
        content: Greek <b>servant of circumcision.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "He also came so that the Gentiles might give glory to God for his
        mercies to them. That is what the psalmist meant when he wrote:\u201CFor
        this, I will praise you among the Gentiles;I will sing praises to your name.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:9 '
        content: Ps 18:49.
    - title: 
      content: "And in another place it is written,\u201CRejoice with his people,you
        Gentiles.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:10 '
        content: Deut 32:43.
    - title: 
      content: "And yet again,\u201CPraise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you
        Gentiles.Praise him, all you people of the earth.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:11 '
        content: Ps 117:1.
    - title: 
      content: "And in another place Isaiah said,\u201CThe heir to David\u2019s throne[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will come,and he will rule over the Gentiles.They will place their hope on
        him.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:12a '
        content: Greek <b>The root of Jesse. </b>David was the son of Jesse.
      - number: '15:12b '
        content: Isa 11:10 (Greek version).
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Reason for Writing"
      content: 'I pray that God, the source of hope, will fill you completely with
        joy and peace because you trust in him. Then you will overflow with confident
        hope through the power of the Holy Spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am fully convinced, my dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that you are full of goodness. You know these things so well you can teach
        each other all about them. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:14 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 15:30.
    - title: 
      content: "Even so, I have been bold enough to write about some of these points,
        knowing that all you need is this reminder. For by God\u2019s grace, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am a special messenger from Christ Jesus to you Gentiles. I bring
        you the Good News so that I might present you as an acceptable offering to
        God, made holy by the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I have reason to be enthusiastic about all Christ Jesus has done
        through me in my service to God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet I dare not boast about anything except what Christ has done through
        me, bringing the Gentiles to God by my message and by the way I worked among
        them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were convinced by the power of miraculous signs and wonders
        and by the power of God\u2019s Spirit.[[COMMENT(0)]] In this way, I have
        fully presented the Good News of Christ from Jerusalem all the way to Illyricum.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:19a '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>the Spirit; </b>still others read <b>the
          Holy Spirit.</b>
      - number: '15:19b '
        content: <b>Illyricum </b>was a region northeast of Italy.
    - title: 
      content: 'My ambition has always been to preach the Good News where the name
        of Christ has never been heard, rather than where a church has already been
        started by someone else. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have been following the plan spoken of in the Scriptures, where
        it says,\u201CThose who have never been told about him will see,and those
        who have never heard of him will understand.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:21 '
        content: Isa 52:15 (Greek version).
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Travel Plans"
      content: 'In fact, my visit to you has been delayed so long because I have
        been preaching in these places.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now I have finished my work in these regions, and after all these
        long years of waiting, I am eager to visit you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am planning to go to Spain, and when I do, I will stop off in Rome.
        And after I have enjoyed your fellowship for a little while, you can provide
        for my journey.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But before I come, I must go to Jerusalem to take a gift to the believers[[COMMENT(0)]]
        there. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:25 '
        content: "Greek <b>God\u2019s holy people; </b>also in 15:26, 31."
    - title: 
      content: 'For you see, the believers in Macedonia and Achaia[[COMMENT(0)]]
        have eagerly taken up an offering for the poor among the believers in Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:26 '
        content: <b>Macedonia </b>and <b>Achaia </b>were the northern and southern
          regions of Greece.
    - title: 
      content: 'They were glad to do this because they feel they owe a real debt
        to them. Since the Gentiles received the spiritual blessings of the Good
        News from the believers in Jerusalem, they feel the least they can do in
        return is to help them financially. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As soon as I have delivered this money and completed this good deed
        of theirs, I will come to see you on my way to Spain. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I am sure that when I come, Christ will richly bless our time
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters, I urge you in the name of our Lord Jesus
        Christ to join in my struggle by praying to God for me. Do this because of
        your love for me, given to you by the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pray that I will be rescued from those in Judea who refuse to obey
        God. Pray also that the believers there will be willing to accept the donation[[COMMENT(0)]]
        I am taking to Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:31 '
        content: Greek <b>the ministry; </b>other manuscripts read <b>the gift.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, by the will of God, I will be able to come to you with a joyful
        heart, and we will be an encouragement to each other.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Paul Greets His Friends
      content: '  I commend to you our sister Phoebe, who is a deacon in the church
        in Cenchrea. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Welcome her in the Lord as one who is worthy of honor among God\u2019s
        people. Help her in whatever she needs, for she has been helpful to many,
        and especially to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give my greetings to Priscilla and Aquila, my co-workers in the ministry
        of Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In fact, they once risked their lives for me. I am thankful to them,
        and so are all the Gentile churches. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also give my greetings to the church that meets in their home.Greet
        my dear friend Epenetus. He was the first person from the province of Asia
        to become a follower of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give my greetings to Mary, who has worked so hard for your benefit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet Andronicus and Junia,[[COMMENT(0)]] my fellow Jews,[[COMMENT(1)]]
        who were in prison with me. They are highly respected among the apostles
        and became followers of Christ before I did. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:7a '
        content: <b>Junia </b>is a feminine name. Some late manuscripts accent the
          word so it reads <b>Junias, </b>a masculine name; still others read <b>Julia
          </b>(feminine).
      - number: '16:7b '
        content: Or <b>compatriots; </b>also in 16:21.
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet Ampliatus, my dear friend in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet Urbanus, our co-worker in Christ, and my dear friend Stachys.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet Apelles, a good man whom Christ approves. And give my greetings
        to the believers from the household of Aristobulus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Greet Herodion, my fellow Jew.[[COMMENT(0)]] Greet the Lord\u2019s
        people from the household of Narcissus. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:11 '
        content: Or <b>compatriot.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Give my greetings to Tryphena and Tryphosa, the Lord\u2019s workers,
        and to dear Persis, who has worked so hard for the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet Rufus, whom the Lord picked out to be his very own; and also
        his dear mother, who has been a mother to me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give my greetings to Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas,
        and the brothers and sisters[[COMMENT(0)]] who meet with them. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers; </b>also in 16:17.
    - title: 
      content: 'Give my greetings to Philologus, Julia, Nereus and his sister, and
        to Olympas and all the believers[[COMMENT(0)]] who meet with them. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:15 '
        content: "Greek <b>all of God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Instructions"
      content: 'Greet each other with a sacred kiss. All the churches of Christ send
        you their greetings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now I make one more appeal, my dear brothers and sisters. Watch
        out for people who cause divisions and upset people\u2019s faith by teaching
        things contrary to what you have been taught. Stay away from them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such people are not serving Christ our Lord; they are serving their
        own personal interests. By smooth talk and glowing words they deceive innocent
        people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But everyone knows that you are obedient to the Lord. This makes
        me very happy. I want you to be wise in doing right and to stay innocent
        of any wrong. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The God of peace will soon crush Satan under your feet. May the grace
        of our Lord Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] be with you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:20 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Lord Jesus Christ.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Timothy, my fellow worker, sends you his greetings, as do Lucius,
        Jason, and Sosipater, my fellow Jews.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, Tertius, the one writing this letter for Paul, send my greetings,
        too, as one of the Lord\u2019s followers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gaius says hello to you. He is my host and also serves as host to
        the whole church. Erastus, the city treasurer, sends you his greetings, and
        so does our brother Quartus.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:23 '
        content: Some manuscripts add verse 24, <b>May the grace of our Lord Jesus
          Christ be with you all. Amen. </b>Still others add this sentence after
          verse 27.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now all glory to God, who is able to make you strong, just as my
        Good News says. This message about Jesus Christ has revealed his plan for
        you Gentiles, a plan kept secret from the beginning of time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now as the prophets[[COMMENT(0)]] foretold and as the eternal
        God has commanded, this message is made known to all Gentiles everywhere,
        so that they too might believe and obey him. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:26 '
        content: Greek <b>the prophetic writings.</b>
